title: The-Laura-Ingraham-Show-Podcast Aug 30
description:
Laura Ingraham August 30, 2016 Podcast
american talk radio conservative

Sowell: 'Welcomes Trump For Reaching Out To African Americans; The NAACP Doesn't Own The Black Community' 
Guest Lineup
Michael Steele - Former Republican National Committee Chairman, MSNBC political analyst.
Pat Buchanan - Former senior advisor to Presidents Nixon, Ford, and Reagan, political commentator, and author.
Thomas Sowell - Senior Fellow on Public Policy at the Hoover Institution, author of Wealth, Poverty, and Politics.

Black Lives Matter to Donald Trump
Heather Mac Donald - Wall Street Journal
Hillary Clinton tried to tar Donald Trump as a racist last week by associating him with the "alt-right." Yet it is Mr. Trump who has decried the loss of black life to violent crime-and has promptly been declared biased for doing so. Whether intentionally or not, Mr. Trump has exposed the hypocrisy of the Black Lives Matter movement and its allies.
Media donates to Clinton Foundation, then downplays the Foundation's scandal
Hillary Clinton and her media allies have been working overtime to put out numerous fires that continue to pop up and spread during the final weeks of her campaign for president. Recently, the flames have gotten more difficult to smother as reports of Clinton's frail health have bled into the mainstream media, despite the unanimous and unilateral decision by the MSM to treat anyone who even raises a question as akin to a Holocaust denier. (On Sunday night, for example, Huffington Post fired contributor David Seaman and deleted his columns simply for linking to a Hillary health video that's been viewed four million times.)
